<paragraph id="166FA336A51CE41CFF14F9761D5D411C" blockId="0.[136,1452,1664,1866]" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
The new species is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="D1D0D8B5A51CE41CFDD6F9761FD14154" authority="C. M. Hu &amp; J. E. Vidal" authorityName="C. M. Hu &amp; J. E. Vidal" box="[586,927,1772,1794]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gracilenta">
<emphasis id="24A47F24A51CE41CFDD6F9761E864157" box="[586,712,1772,1793]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">A. gracilenta</emphasis>
C.M. Hu &amp; J.E. Vidal
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D1D0D8B5A51CE41CFC52F97619474154" authority="C. M. Hu &amp; J. E. Vidal" authorityName="C. M. Hu &amp; J. E. Vidal" box="[974,1289,1772,1794]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pitardii">
<emphasis id="24A47F24A51CE41CFC52F97618614157" box="[974,1071,1772,1793]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">A. pitardii</emphasis>
C.M. Hu &amp; J.E. Vidal
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from both by being glabrous throughout, leaves with pellucid glandular stripes, inflorescence compound umbellate, and with slender pedicels.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="166FA336A51CE41FFF14F8E218FF478E" blockId="0.[136,1451,1912,2083]" lastBlockId="3.[136,1452,158,1265]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="66" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
Shrubs to 
<quantity id="D1280ED3A51CE41CFF63F8E21D0C41C5" box="[255,322,1912,1939]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" unit="m" value="1.5">1.5 m</quantity>
tall, glabrous throughout; branchlets ± angulate and slightly dilated at insertion. Leaves alternate, equidistant along the branchlets; petiole 
<quantity id="D1280ED3A51CE41CFDC8F8061E9C41E1" box="[596,722,1948,1975]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" unit="cm" value="2.0" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2.5 cm</quantity>
long, channeled adaxially; blade elliptic-lanceolate, (6) 
<quantity id="D1280ED3A51CE41CFAD4F80619E541E1" box="[1352,1451,1948,1975]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" unit="cm" value="10.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="8.0">8–13 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="D1280ED3A51CE41CFF54F85A1D55418D" box="[200,283,1984,2011]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" unit="cm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 cm</quantity>
wide, gradually tapered to the base, apex acuminate, margin entire, thickly chartaceous, adaxial surface dark green, abaxial surface paler and often turning brownish when dry, with scattered translucent glandular stripes (visible under trans-illumination); midrib narrowly impressed above, raised beneath; lateral nerves 11–13 on each side of midrib, with short intermediaters, very slender, indistinct or faint, angle to the midrib about 50°, arcuate upward, not forming an uniform intramarginal vein, reticulation of veins invisible. Inflorescences axillary near apex of branches, compound umbellate; peduncle 
<quantity id="D1280ED3A51FE41FFE75FF7C1E1E4757" box="[489,592,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" unit="cm" value="3.25" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5–4 cm</quantity>
long; primary rays 2–4, slender, 
<quantity id="D1280ED3A51FE41FFC24FF7C18504757" box="[952,1054,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" unit="cm" value="1.4" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.0">1–1.8 cm</quantity>
long, almost horizontally spreading out from peduncle, each bearing 2–4 umbellately arranged flowers; pedicels 
<quantity id="D1280ED3A51FE41FFC6DFE9018104773" box="[1009,1118,266,293]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="10.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="8.0">8–12 mm</quantity>
long, filiform. Calyx whitish green, ca. 
<quantity id="D1280ED3A51FE41FFE9EFEB41D12471F" box="[258,348,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
long, split nearly to base; lobes broadly ovate, apex broadly acute, tip blunt, margin minutely ciliolate, not punctate. Corolla light purple, ca. 
<quantity id="D1280ED3A51FE41FFD06FEC81EBE473B" box="[666,752,338,365]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
long, rotate, deeply lobed almost to base, lobes broadly ovate, ca. 
<quantity id="D1280ED3A51FE41FFF33FEEC1CBF47C7" box="[175,241,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="D1280ED3A51FE41FFEA4FEEC1DC147C7" box="[312,399,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
wide, apex acute, margin ciliolate towards base. Stamen filaments purple, broadly triangular; anthers narrowly ovate, longer than filaments, ca. 
<quantity id="D1280ED3A51FE41FFD52FE001F6947E3" box="[718,807,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
long, apiculate. Ovary superior, ovoid; style protruding beyond stamens, ca. 
<quantity id="D1280ED3A51FE41FFEEDFE241D89478F" box="[369,455,446,473]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
long; ovules ca. 10, arranged irregularly in 2–3 series on placenta.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
